{"name":"Linked Phantom Armor, Gladiator (CR2)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 11</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Linked Phantom Armor, Gladiator with SBC</button></p><section id=\"LinkedPhantomArmorGladiator\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Linked Phantom Armor, Gladiator</p><p>CR 2</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 600</p><p>Variant phantom armor (<em>Pathfinder Bestiary 4</em> 213)</p><p>NE Medium undead</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +5; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.; Perception +6</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 21, touch 11, flat-footed 20 (+9 armor, +1 Dex, +1 shield)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 13 each (3d8)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +1, <strong>Ref</strong> +2, <strong>Will</strong> +3</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> channel resistance +2; <strong>Immune</strong> undead traits</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft.</p><p><strong>Melee</strong><em>+1 trident</em> +5 (1d8+3)</p><p><strong>Space</strong> 10 ft.; <strong>Reach</strong> 10 ft.</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 14, <strong>Dex</strong> 13, <strong>Con</strong> &mdash;, <strong>Int</strong> 7, <strong>Wis</strong> 11, <strong>Cha</strong> 10</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +2; <strong>CMB</strong> +4; <strong>CMD</strong> 15</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Improved Initiative, Power Attack</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +6, Stealth +7</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Sylvan (can&rsquo;t speak)</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> freeze (suit of armor)</p><p><strong>Gear</strong><em>+1 trident</em></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>SPECIAL ABILITIES</strong></p></div><hr /><div><strong>End of Watch (Su)</strong> If a linked phantom armor is destroyed, the suit of armor falls to the ground, but at the start of the next round, if that phantom armor&rsquo;s counterpart remains active, the fallen phantom armor stands once more, restored to 10 hp. Only if both the young and mature counterparts of the same phantom armor are both destroyed in the same round do they remain defeated.</div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"0x6lahYcbStMjnum"}
{"name":"Candlewick (CR 9)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 32</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Candlewick with SBC</button></p><section id=\"Candlewick\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Candlewick</p><p>CR 9</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 6,400</p><p>CN Small fey</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +16; <strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision; Perception +20</p><p><strong>Aura</strong> shining light (20 ft.)</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 24, touch 24, flat-footed 18 (+5 Dex, +1 dodge, +7 insight, +1 size)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 110 (13d6+65)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +9, <strong>Ref</strong> +13, <strong>Will</strong> +12</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> all-around vision, amorphous, fated; <strong>Immune</strong> blindness, light-based effects; <strong>SR</strong> 20</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> fly 40 ft. (perfect)</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> 4 searing tendrils +12 touch (2d6 fire)</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> sneak attack +1d6</p><strong>Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 7th; concentration +14)<br />Constant&mdash;<em>tongues</em><br />At will&mdash;<em>dancing lights</em>, <em>daylight</em>, <em>dimension door</em> (only to locations in reach of its shining light), <em>searing light</em><br />3/day&mdash;<em>mirror image</em>, <em>misdirection</em><br />1/day&mdash;<em>displacement</em></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 10, <strong>Dex</strong> 20, <strong>Con</strong> 20, <strong>Int</strong> 14, <strong>Wis</strong> 18, <strong>Cha</strong> 24</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +6; <strong>CMB</strong> +5; <strong>CMD</strong> 35 (can&rsquo;t be tripped)</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Combat Reflexes, Defensive Combat Training, Dodge, Flyby Attack, Improved Initiative, Mobility, Skill Focus (Bluff)</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Acrobatics +21, Bluff +29, Fly +31, Knowledge (arcana) +15, Knowledge (nature) +18, Perception +20, Perform (dance) +23, Sense Motive +20</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Aklo, Common, Sylvan; tongues</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> refraction</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>ECOLOCY</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Environment</strong> any</p><p><strong>Organization</strong> solitary, glow (2&ndash;5), or troupe (1&ndash;6 candlewicks plus other fey)</p><p><strong>Treasure</strong> none</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>SPECIAL ABILITIES</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Fated (Su)</strong> A candlewick adds its Charisma modifier as an insight bonus to AC and on Initiative checks.</p><p><strong>Searing Tendrils (Su)</strong> A candlewick&rsquo;s searing tendrils are primary attacks.</p><p><strong>Refraction (Su)</strong> Once per day as a standard action, a candlewick can create seven shimmering duplicates of itself which appear anywhere within 60 feet of the candlewick and last a number of rounds equal to the candlewick&rsquo;s Charisma modifier (typically 7 rounds). These refractions are identical to the original in all respects except that when conjured they have a number of hit points equal to 20% of the true candlewick&rsquo;s maximum hit points (22 hit points for a typical candlewick). The refractions have all of the true candlewick&rsquo;s melee attacks and abilities, except they can only make one searing tendril attack each, can&rsquo;t use spell-like abilities, and can&rsquo;t use refraction. All refractions take their turn immediately after their creator candlewick&rsquo;s turn concludes. Refractions take double damage from spells with the darkness or shadow descriptor. If the candlewick is slain, is rendered unconscious, or is ever more than 60 feet from a refraction, the affected refractions instantly vanish.</p><p><strong>Shining Light (Su)</strong> A candlewick radiates bright light in a 20-foot radius. It can suppress this aura for 1 round as a move action. This light counters magical darkness effects as if it were a 5th level spell effect.</p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"0ymmIJgfsWZSllsZ"}
