{"name":"Quishu (CR —)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 7</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Quishu with SBC</button></p><section id=\"Quishu\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Quishu</p><p>CR &mdash;</p></div><div><p>Biped fey eidolon</p><p>LE Medium outsider</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +2; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft., low-light vision; Perception +0</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 24, touch 13, flat-footed 21 (+2 Dex, +1 dodge, +11 natural)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 59 (7d10+21)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +7, <strong>Ref</strong> +4, <strong>Will</strong> +5 (+4 morale bonus vs. enchantment spells and effects)</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> evasion</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft., fly 30 ft. (good)</p><p><strong>Melee</strong><em>+1 axiomatic earth breaker</em> +12/+7 (2d6+7/&times;3 plus 2d6 vs. chaotic)</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> breath weapon (30-foot cone, 7d6 electricity, Reflex DC 18, 1/day)</p><p><strong>Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 7th; concentration +7)<br />At will&mdash;<em>dancing lights</em>, <em>prestidigitation</em><br />3/day&mdash;<em>grease</em> (DC 11)</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 19, <strong>Dex</strong> 15, <strong>Con</strong> 14, <strong>Int</strong> 7, <strong>Wis</strong> 10, <strong>Cha</strong> 11</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +7; <strong>CMB</strong> +11; <strong>CMD</strong> 24</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Ability Focus (breath weapon), Dodge, Improved Natural Armor, Toughness</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Acrobatics +12, Disable Device +18, Fly +16, Use Magic Device +10; Racial Modifiers +8 Disable Device</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Common</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> devotion, evolutions (breath weapon, flight [wings], improved natural armor, limbs [arms, legs], low-light vision, skilled [Disable Device], weapon training martial, weapon training simple), woodland stride</p><p><strong>Other Gear</strong><em>+1 axiomatic earth breaker</em><sup>UE</sup></p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"ByDj935vvRY8Qbi3"}
{"name":"Samley (fighter 5/gunslinger 5)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 23</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Samley with SBC</button></p><section id=\"Samley\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Samley</p><p>CR 9</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 6,400</p><p>Male half-orc fighter 5/gunslinger 5 (<em>Pathfinder RPG Ultimate Combat</em> 9)</p><p>N Medium humanoid (human, orc)</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +5; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.; Perception +8</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 22, touch 15, flat-footed 18 (+7 armor, +1 deflection, +3 Dex, +1 dodge)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 104 (10d10+45)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +12, <strong>Ref</strong> +9, <strong>Will</strong> +5 (+1 vs. fear)</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> orc ferocity</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft. (20 ft. in armor)</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> masterwork light flail +12/+7 (1d8+1)</p><p><strong>Ranged</strong><em>+1 blunderbuss</em> +16 (1d8+7/19&ndash;20)</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> deeds (deadeye, gunslinger initiative, gunslinger&rsquo;s dodge, pistol-whip, quick clear, utility shot), grit (1), gun training +3 (blunderbuss), weapon training (firearms +1<sup>UC</sup>)</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>TACTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>During Combat</strong> Samley lets his clockwork guardian protect him while he uses his blunderbuss to attack.</p><p><strong>Morale</strong> Samley fights to the death.<strong><br /></strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 12, <strong>Dex</strong> 16, <strong>Con</strong> 16, <strong>Int</strong> 8, <strong>Wis</strong> 10, <strong>Cha</strong> 16</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +10; <strong>CMB</strong> +11; <strong>CMD</strong> 26</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Deadly Aim, Dodge, Gunsmithing<sup>UC</sup>, Improved Critical (blunderbuss), Iron Will, Master Craftsman, Rapid Reload, Toughness, Weapon Focus (blunderbuss), Weapon Specialization (blunderbuss)</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Craft (clockwork) +15, Craft (firearms) +5, Intimidate +5, Perception +8; Racial Modifiers +2 Intimidate</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Orc</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> armor training 1, construct crafter, gunsmith, orc blood</p><p><strong>Gear</strong><em>+1 breastplate</em>, <em>+1 blunderbuss</em><sup>UC</sup>, masterwork light flail, <em>belt of mighty constitution +2</em>, <em>cloak of resistance +1</em>, <em>ring of protection +1</em>, glowing screwdriver (skill blessing for Craft [clockworks] leanan sidhe token)</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>SPECIAL ABILITIES</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Construct Crafter (Ex)</strong> Although Samley isn&rsquo;t a spellcaster, his great skill and understanding of clockworks allows him to craft these constructions without having to meet the spellcasting requirements, although it takes him twice as long to build a construct in this manner and increases the Craft DC by 5.</p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"FuwktzaZgvr9ous0"}
{"name":"The Host (sorcerer 6)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 14</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import The Host with SBC</button></p><section id=\"TheHost\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">The Host</p><p>CR 8</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 6,400</p><p>Male sentient wax golem sorcerer 6 (<em>Pathfinder Bestiary 4</em> 133)</p><p>N Medium construct</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +5; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft., low-light vision; Perception +6</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 22, touch 12, flat-footed 20 (+4 armor, +1 Dex, +1 dodge, +6 natural)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 69 (10 HD; 4d10+6d6+26)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +3, <strong>Ref</strong> +6, <strong>Will</strong> +9</p><p><strong>Immune</strong> cold, construct traits, magic</p><p><strong>Weaknesses</strong> vulnerable to fire</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft.</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> slam +10 (1d6+4)</p><p><strong>Bloodline Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 6th; concentration +9)<br />6/day&mdash;<em>laughing touch</em></p><p><strong>Sorcerer Spells Known</strong> (CL 6th; concentration +9)<br />3rd (4/day)&mdash;<em>protection from fire</em><br />2nd (6/day)&mdash;<em>hideous laughter</em> (DC 15), <em>mirror image</em>, <em>web</em> (DC 15)<br />1st (7/day)&mdash;<em>entangle</em> (DC 14), <em>mage armor</em>, <em>magic missile</em>, <em>shield</em>, <em>true strike</em><br />0 (at will)&mdash;<em>dancing lights</em>, <em>daze</em> (DC 13), <em>detect magic</em>, <em>ghost sound</em> (DC 13), <em>mage hand</em>, <em>resistance</em>, <em>read magic</em><br /><strong>Bloodline</strong> fey</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>TACTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Before Combat</strong> The Host casts <em>mage armor</em> before combat.</p><p><strong>During Combat</strong> The Host casts <em>protection from fire</em> on himself, then activates his <em>winged boots</em> and moves off the path, hoping to trick the PCs into following him as he flies over the illusory ground. He then casts <em>mirror image</em>, and on the following rounds uses his offensive spells on the PCs.</p><p><strong>Morale</strong> The Host flees to area <strong>A9</strong> if reduced to below 20 hp, but if confronted there fights until destroyed.<strong><br /></strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 16, <strong>Dex</strong> 13, <strong>Con</strong> &mdash;, <strong>Int</strong> 10, <strong>Wis</strong> 13, <strong>Cha</strong> 16</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +7; <strong>CMB</strong> +10; <strong>CMD</strong> 22</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Combat Casting, Dodge, Eschew Materials, Improved Initiative, Iron Will, Lightning Reflexes</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Knowledge (arcana) +8, Perception +6, Sense Motive +6, Spellcraft +8</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Sylvan</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> conditional sentience, bloodline arcana (+2 DC for compulsion spells), woodland stride</p><p><strong>Gear</strong><em>winged boots</em></p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"HHHngHDS3h56v6Cu"}
{"name":"Wo Gun (unchained summoner 9)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 20</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Wo Gun with SBC</button></p><section id=\"WoGun\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Wo Gun</p><p>CR 8</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 4,800</p><p>Male human unchained summoner 9 (<em>Pathfinder Unchained</em> 25)</p><p>LE Medium humanoid (human)</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +2; <strong>Senses</strong> Perception +0</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 22, touch 13, flat-footed 16 (+5 armor, +1 deflection, +2 Dex, +4 natural)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 71 (9d8+27)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +5, <strong>Ref</strong> +5, <strong>Will</strong> +6</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> shield ally</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft. (20 ft. in armor)</p><p><strong>Melee</strong><em>+1 cestus</em> +6/+1 (1d4/19&ndash;20)</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> maker&rsquo;s call 1/day, transposition</p><p><strong>Summoner (Unchained) Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 9th; concentration +14)<br />8/day&mdash;<em>summon monster V</em></p><p><strong>Summoner Spells Known</strong> (CL 9th; concentration +14)<br />3rd (4/day)&mdash;<em>displacement</em>, <em>haste</em>, <em>heroism</em>, <em>shield companion</em><sup>ACG</sup><br />2nd (5/day)&mdash;<em>barkskin</em>, <em>lesser evolution surge</em><sup>APG</sup> (DC 17), <em>invisibility</em>, <em>resist energy</em><br />1st (7/day)&mdash;<em>ant haul</em><sup>APG</sup> (DC 16), <em>grease</em>, <em>lesser rejuvenate eidolon</em><sup>APG</sup>, <em>shield</em>, <em>unseen servant</em><br />0 (at will)&mdash;<em>acid splash</em>, <em>detect magic</em>, <em>guidance</em>, <em>light</em>, <em>mage hand</em>, <em>mending</em></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>TACTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Before Combat</strong> Wo Gun casts <em>barkskin</em> on himself.</p><p><strong>During Combat</strong> Wo Gun casts <em>haste</em> on first round of combat, then allows his eidolon and terra-cotta soldiers to engage foes in melee while he hangs back and summons monsters or casts offensive spells. He casts <em>shield companion</em> on his eidolon after it is hit the first time in combat.</p><p><strong>Morale</strong> Wo Gun fights to the death.<strong><br /></strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 8, <strong>Dex</strong> 14, <strong>Con</strong> 14, <strong>Int</strong> 12, <strong>Wis</strong> 10, <strong>Cha</strong> 20</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +6; <strong>CMB</strong> +5; <strong>CMD</strong> 18</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Craft Construct, Craft Magic Arms &amp; Armor, Craft Wondrous Item, Extra Evolution (2)<sup>UM</sup>, Skill Focus (Craft [sculpture])</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Craft (clockwork) +11, Craft (sculpture) +18, Knowledge (arcana) +13, Spellcraft +13</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Tien</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> bond senses (9 rounds/day), eidolon (named Quishu), life link</p><p><strong>Other Gear</strong><em>+1 chain shirt</em>, <em>+1 cestus</em><sup>APG</sup>, <em>headband of alluring charisma +2</em>, <em>ring of protection +1</em>, masterwork sculpting tools, glowing chisel (spell blessing leanan sidhe token)</p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"Hxr3DFMpi72o3SZ8"}
{"name":"Phantom General (fighter 5)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 11</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Phantom General with SBC</button></p><section id=\"PhantomGeneral\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Phantom General</p><p>CR 9</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 6,400</p><p>Giant phantom armor fighter 5 (<em>Pathfinder Bestiary 4</em> 213)</p><p>NE Large undead</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +6; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.; Perception +9</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 21, touch 12, flat-footed 18 (+9 armor, +2 Dex, +1 dodge, &ndash;1 size)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 114 (10 HD; 5d8+5d10+65)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +10, <strong>Ref</strong> +4, <strong>Will</strong> +6 (+1 vs. fear)</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> bravery +1, channel resistance +4, eternal watch; <strong>Immune</strong> undead traits</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 20 ft.</p><p><strong>Melee</strong><em>+2 ranseur</em> +18/+13 (2d6+14/19&ndash;20/&times;3)</p><p><strong>Space</strong> 10 ft.; <strong>Reach</strong> 10 ft.</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> weapon training (polearms +1)</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 22, <strong>Dex</strong> 15, <strong>Con</strong> &mdash;, <strong>Int</strong> 7, <strong>Wis</strong> 13, <strong>Cha</strong> 20</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +8; <strong>CMB</strong> +15; <strong>CMD</strong> 28</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Combat Reflexes, Dodge, Improved Critical (ranseur), Improved Initiative, Power Attack, Toughness, Weapon Focus (ranseur), Weapon Specialization (ranseur)</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Intimidate +18, Perception +9</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Sylvan (can&rsquo;t speak)</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> freeze (suit of armor), armor training 1</p><p><strong>Gear</strong><em>+2 ranseur</em></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>SPECIAL ABILITIES</strong></p></div><hr /><div><strong>Eternal Watch (Su)</strong> If the phantom general is destroyed, the suit of armor falls to the ground, but at the start of the next round, if any linked phantom armors remain active, the phantom general stands once more, restored to 50 hp. The phantom general remains at rest only if it is destroyed after all 10 of the linked phantom armors are destroyed.</div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"MAWE1VoHy6kgLngj"}
{"name":"Glowdrop (bard 5)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 7</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Glowdrop with SBC</button></p><section id=\"Glowdrop\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Glowdrop</p><p>CR 11</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 12,800</p><p>Male candlewick bard 5 (page 32)</p><p>CN Small fey</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +20; <strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision; Perception +26</p><p><strong>Aura</strong> shining light (20 ft.)</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 28, touch 28, flat-footed 20 (+7 Dex, +1 dodge, +9 insight, +1 size)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 144 (18 HD; 13d6+5d8+77)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +9, <strong>Ref</strong> +19, <strong>Will</strong> +17; +4 vs. bardic performance, language-dependent, and sonic</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> all-around vision, amorphous; <strong>Immune</strong> blindness, light-based effects; <strong>SR</strong> 20</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> fly 40 ft. (perfect)</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> 4 searing tendrils +15 touch (2d8 fire/19&ndash;20)</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> bardic performance 21 rounds/day (countersong, distraction, fascinate [DC 21], inspire competence +2, inspire courage +2), sneak attack +1d6</p><p><strong>Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 7th; concentration +16)<br />Constant&mdash;<em>tongues</em><br />At will&mdash;<em>dancing lights</em>, <em>daylight</em>, <em>dimension door</em> (only to locations in reach of its shining light), <em>searing light</em><br />3/day&mdash;<em>mirror image</em>, <em>misdirection</em><br />1/day&mdash;<em>displacement</em></p><p><strong>Bard Spells Known</strong> (CL 5th; concentration +14)<br />2nd (4/day)&mdash;<em>cure moderate wounds</em>, <em>darkness</em>, <em>suggestion</em> (DC 21)<br />1st (7/day)&mdash;<em>cure light wounds</em>, <em>hideous laughter</em> (DC20), <em>identify</em>, <em>liberating command</em><sup>UC</sup><br />0 (at will)&mdash;<em>daze</em> (DC 19), <em>detect magic</em>, <em>ghost sound</em> (DC 19), <em>mage hand</em>, <em>open/close</em>, <em>prestidigitation</em></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>TACTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Before Combat</strong> Glowdrop maintains <em>misdirection</em> on himself at all times and is eager to lie about the source of this effect if the PCs confront him.</p><p><strong>During Combat</strong> To support the PCs, Glowdrop uses inspire courage while staying out of combat. He&rsquo;ll use healing on the PCs as needed. In a real confrontation against the PCs, Glowdrop&rsquo;s first act is to refract, and then to cast <em>mirror image</em> and then <em>displacement</em>. Glowdrop uses inspire courage on his refractions, then works with them to flank foes and maximize sneak attacks.</p><p><strong>Morale</strong> Glowdrop fights to the death, as he fears punishment from the Lantern King should he fail to complete his orders.<strong><br /></strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 10, <strong>Dex</strong> 24, <strong>Con</strong> 18, <strong>Int</strong> 16, <strong>Wis</strong> 20, <strong>Cha</strong> 29</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +9; <strong>CMB</strong> +8; <strong>CMD</strong> 44 (can&rsquo;t be tripped)</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Combat Casting, Combat Reflexes, Defensive Combat Training, Dodge, Flyby Attack, Improved Critical (searing tendril), Improved Initiative, Mobility, Skill Focus (Bluff)</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Acrobatics +28, Bluff +36, Diplomacy +30, Fly +38, Knowledge (arcana) +26, Knowledge (nature) +26, Perception +26, Perform (dance) +30, Sense Motive +26</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Aklo, Common, Sylvan; <em>tongues</em></p><p><strong>SQ</strong> bardic knowledge +2, lore master 1/day, refraction, versatile performance (dance)</p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"OtlMsewsBEA2664Y"}
{"name":"Linked Phantom Armor, Fencer (CR 2)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 11</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Linked Phantom Armor, Fencer with SBC</button></p><section id=\"LinkedPhantomArmorFencer\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Linked Phantom Armor, Fencer</p><p>CR 2</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 600</p><p>Variant phantom armor (<em>Pathfinder Bestiary 4</em> 213)</p><p>NE Medium undead</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +5; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.; Perception +6</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 21, touch 11, flat-footed 20 (+9 armor, +1 Dex, +1 shield)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 13 each (3d8)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +1, <strong>Ref</strong> +2, <strong>Will</strong> +3</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> channel resistance +2; <strong>Immune</strong> undead traits</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft.</p><p><strong>Melee</strong><em>+1 rapier</em> +5 (1d6+3/18&ndash;20)</p><p><strong>Space</strong> 10 ft.; <strong>Reach</strong> 10 ft.</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 14, <strong>Dex</strong> 13, <strong>Con</strong> &mdash;, <strong>Int</strong> 7, <strong>Wis</strong> 11, <strong>Cha</strong> 10</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +2; <strong>CMB</strong> +4; <strong>CMD</strong> 15</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Improved Initiative, Power Attack</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +6, Stealth +7</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Sylvan (can&rsquo;t speak)</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> freeze (suit of armor)</p><p><strong>Gear</strong><em>+1 rapier</em></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>SPECIAL ABILITIES</strong></p></div><hr /><div><strong>End of Watch (Su)</strong> If a linked phantom armor is destroyed, the suit of armor falls to the ground, but at the start of the next round, if that phantom armor&rsquo;s counterpart remains active, the fallen phantom armor stands once more, restored to 10 hp. Only if both the young and mature counterparts of the same phantom armor are both destroyed in the same round do they remain defeated.</div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"YFxokNDAVcFV3GRq"}
{"name":"Jeralbeena (bard 11)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 22</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Jeralbeena with SBC</button></p><section id=\"Jeralbeena\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Jeralbeena</p><p>CR 10</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 9,600</p><p>Female gnome bard 11</p><p>CN Small humanoid (gnome)</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +2; <strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision; Perception +15</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 21, touch 14, flat-footed 18 (+5 armor, +2 Dex, +1 dodge, +2 shield, +1 size)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 108 (11d8+55)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +6, <strong>Ref</strong> +9, <strong>Will</strong> +6; +2 vs. illusions, +4 vs. bardic performance, language-dependent, and sonic</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> defensive training</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 20 ft.</p><p><strong>Melee</strong><em>+1 construct-bane adamantine light mace</em> +13/+8 (1d4 plus 2d6 vs. constructs)</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> bardic performance 28 rounds/day (move action; countersong, dirge of doom, distraction, fascinate [DC 19], inspire competence +4, inspire courage +3, inspire greatness, suggestion [DC 19]), hatred</p><p><strong>Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 11th; concentration +15)<br />1/day&mdash;<em>dancing lights</em>, <em>ghost sound</em> (DC 15), <em>prestidigitation</em>, <em>speak with animals</em></p><p><strong>Bard Spells Known</strong> (CL 11th; concentration +15)<br />4th (3/day)&mdash;<em>cure critical wounds</em>, <em>dance of a hundred cuts</em><sup>UM</sup>, <em>shout</em> (DC 18)<br />3rd (5/day)&mdash;<em>cure serious wounds</em>, <em>displacement</em>, <em>haste</em>, <em>thundering drums</em><sup>APG</sup> (DC 17)<br />2nd (5/day)&mdash;<em>cure moderate wounds</em>, <em>invisibility</em>, <em>mirror image</em>, <em>shatter</em> (DC 16), <em>sound burst</em> (DC 16)<br />1st (6/day)&mdash;<em>chord of shards</em><sup>UM</sup> (DC 15), <em>cure light wounds</em>, <em>ear-piercing scream</em><sup>UM</sup> (DC 15), <em>saving finale</em><sup>APG</sup> (DC 15), <em>unseen servant</em>, <em>vanish</em><sup>APG</sup> (DC 16)<br />0 (at will)&mdash;<em>detect magic</em>, <em>light</em>, <em>mage hand</em>, <em>mending</em>, <em>prestidigitation</em>, <em>summon instrument</em></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>TACTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>During Combat</strong> Jeralbeena starts combat by activating inspire courage, then casts <em>invisibility</em>, <em>displacement</em>, <em>mirror image</em>, and <em>haste</em> before using her spells and attacking with her mace. She&rsquo;ll start melee with <em>dance of a hundred cuts</em> and tries to stay mobile even after that effect wears off, to limit full attacks against herself.</p><p><strong>Morale</strong> Jeralbeena fights to the death.<strong><br /></strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 8, <strong>Dex</strong> 14, <strong>Con</strong> 16, <strong>Int</strong> 12, <strong>Wis</strong> 8, <strong>Cha</strong> 18</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +8; <strong>CMB</strong> +6; <strong>CMD</strong> 19</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Craft Wondrous Item, Dodge, Skill Focus (Stealth), Toughness, Weapon Finesse, Weapon Focus (light mace)</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Craft (musical instruments) +19, Perception +15, Perform (percussion instruments) +18, Perform (string instruments) +18, Perform (wind instruments) +18, Spellcraft +15, Stealth +26</p><p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Draconic, Gnome, Sylvan</p><p><strong>SQ</strong> bardic knowledge +5, gnome magic, jack-of-all-trades, lore master 2/day, versatile performances (percussion, string, wind)</p><p><strong>Gear</strong><em>one-person orchestra</em>, <em>+1 buckler</em>, <em>+1 construct-bane adamantine light mace</em>, masterwork instrument crafting tools, glowing tuning fork (spell blessing leanan sidhe token)</p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"j2HZFyhsNpHCDTGp"}
{"name":"Toy Soldier Swarm (CR 8)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 33</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Toy Soldier Swarm with SBC</button></p><section id=\"ToySoldierSwarm\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Toy Soldier Swarm</p><p>CR 8</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 4,800</p><p>N Diminutive construct (swarm)</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +10; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft., low-light vision; Perception +0</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 21, touch 15, flat-footed 15 (+6 Dex, +6 natural, &ndash;1 size)</p><p><strong>hp</strong> 85 (10d10+30)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +3, <strong>Ref</strong> +11, <strong>Will</strong> +3</p><p><strong>Immune</strong> construct traits, swarm traits, weapon damage</p><p><strong>Weaknesses</strong> vulnerable to electricity</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft.</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> swarm (3d6 plus distraction)</p><p><strong>Space</strong> 10 ft.; <strong>Reach</strong> 0 ft.</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> distraction (DC 17), volley, reactive tactics</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str</strong> 10, <strong>Dex</strong> 22, <strong>Con</strong> &mdash;, <strong>Int</strong> &mdash;, <strong>Wis</strong> 10, <strong>Cha</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Base Atk</strong> +10; <strong>CMB</strong> &mdash;; <strong>CMD</strong> &mdash;</p><p><strong>Feats</strong> Ability Focus (distraction)<sup>B</sup>, Improved Initiative<sup>B</sup>, Lightning Reflexes<sup>B</sup></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>SPECIAL ABILITIES</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Reactive Tactics (Ex)</strong> A toy soldier swarm&rsquo;s tactics adjust and change during battle depending upon how badly it was damaged in the previous round. <strong>Start of Combat:</strong> At the start of any combat, a toy soldier swarm&rsquo;s statistics are unmodified; a toy soldier reverts to this mode after 1 minute of not engaging in combat. <strong>Offensive Tactics:</strong> At the start of any round after which the toy soldier swarm took fewer than 15 points of damage during the previous round, the soldiers become more violent at the expense of defense. The swarm takes a &ndash;2 penalty to its AC but inflicts 4d6 damage with its swarm attack and the save DC of its distraction ability increases to DC 19. Defensive Tactics: At the start of any round after which the toy soldier swarm took more than 15 points of damage during the previous round, the soldiers adopt defensive tactics. The swarm&rsquo;s damage is reduced to 2d6 and the save DC for distraction to DC 15, but it gains a +2 dodge bonus to its AC and a +2 circumstance bonus to all saving throws. <strong>Desperate Tactics:</strong> At the start of any round during which a toy soldier swarm has fewer than 10 hp, it adopts defensive tactics and deals only 1d6 damage with its swarm and does not distract, but it does gain fast healing 20. A toy soldier swarm cannot perform desperate tactics two rounds in a row.</p><p><strong>Volley (Ex)</strong> Up to three times a day, if a toy soldier swarm cannot reach a foe within sight to inflict swarm damage, it can fire a volley of tiny missiles (typically arrows or spears) to a range of 20 feet. All creatures in a 10-foot-radius burst take 6d6 points of piercing damage from the volley (DC 21 Reflex half).</p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Puzzle_Box.jpg","_id":"kS7X1Nn5ewWdwK6Z"}
{"name":"Lumestin (sorcerer 7)","permission":{"default":0,"IPeKQhMz2Odi77tR":3},"content":"<p><strong>Source </strong>The Puzzle Box, p. 27</p><p><button class=\"importStatblock\">Import Lumestin with SBC</button></p><section id=\"Lumestin\"><div class=\"heading\"><p class=\"alignleft\">Lumestin</p><p>CR 12/MR 3</p></div><div><p><strong>XP</strong> 19,200</p><p>Male leanan sidhe sorcerer 7 (<em>Pathfinder RPG Bestiary 4</em> 180)</p><p>CN Medium fey (mythic)</p><p><strong>Init</strong> +12; <strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision; Perception +25</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>DEFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>AC</strong> 29, touch 23, flat-footed 23 (+7 deflection, +5 Dex, +1 dodge, +6 natural)</p><p>hp 159 (18d6+97)</p><p><strong>Fort</strong> +16, <strong>Ref</strong> +21, <strong>Will</strong> +19</p><p><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> fated (+2); <strong>DR</strong> 10/cold iron and epic</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>OFFENSE</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft., fly 30 ft. (good)</p><p><strong>Melee</strong><em>+2 brilliant energy dagger</em> +12/+7 (1d4+4/19&ndash;20) or touch +5 (1d4 Cha damage)</p><p><strong>Special Attacks</strong> life drain, mythic power (3/day, surge +1d6)</p><p><strong>Leanan Sidhe Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 10th; concentration +17)<br />Constant&mdash;<em>tongues</em><br />At will&mdash;<em>calm emotions</em> (DC 20), <em>crushing despair</em> (DC 22), <em>dimension door</em> (self plus 50 lbs. of objects only)<br />3/day&mdash;<em>animal trance</em> (DC 20), quickened <em>charm person</em> (DC 19)</p><p><strong>Sorcerer Spell-Like Abilities</strong> (CL 7th; concentration +14)<br />10/day&mdash;touch of destiny (+3)</p><p><strong>Sorcerer Spells Known</strong> (CL 7th; concentration +14)<br />3rd (6/day)&mdash;<em>daylight</em>, <em>dispel magic</em>, <em>protection from energy</em><br />2nd (8/day)&mdash;<em>blur</em>, <em>darkness</em>, <em>glitterdust</em> (DC 19), <em>mirror image